{
  "text": "Traditionally, pathogenic Leptospira are classified into more than 200 serovars based on serological methods [CITATION_1] . Nowadays, multilocus sequence typing (MLST) method has been recently proved for typing leptospires [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . MLST is a simple PCR based technique, which makes use of automated DNA sequencers to assign and characterize the alleles present in different target genes. The selected loci are generally the housekeeping genes, which evolve very slowly over an evolutionary time-scale [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] and hence qualify as highly robust markers of ancient and modern ancestry. The sequencing of multiple loci provides a balance between technical feasibility and resolution.",
